---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Cookies & Tokens collects, uses, and protects information, including data handled through advertising platforms such as the Google Ads API."
  meta="Last updated: 17 June 2026"
>
  <p>
    Cookies &amp; Tokens ("Cookies &amp; Tokens", "we", "us", or "our") is a
    creative, growth, and software studio. This Privacy Policy explains what
    information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have. It applies
    to our website at
    <a href="https://www.cookiesandtokens.com">cookiesandtokens.com</a>, and to
    the services we provide to our clients.
  </p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    We help brands with creative, marketing and growth, and software. As part of
    our growth services, we plan, build, and manage digital advertising
    campaigns on behalf of our clients across platforms such as Google Ads, and
    we build internal tools that connect to those platforms' APIs.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Information you give us.</strong> When you contact us by email or
      through our website, we receive your name, email address, and anything you
      choose to include in your message.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Usage information.</strong> When you visit our website, we may
      collect standard technical data such as your IP address, browser type,
      pages viewed, and referring page, through cookies and similar technologies.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Client and campaign data.</strong> When we deliver services to a
      client, we process data the client authorizes us to access, which can
      include advertising accounts, campaign performance metrics, and analytics.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to enquiries and provide the services you or your company request.</li>
    <li>To plan, run, measure, and optimize advertising campaigns for our clients.</li>
    <li>To operate, maintain, and improve our website and internal tools.</li>
    <li>To meet legal, accounting, and security obligations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Advertising platforms and the Google Ads API</h2>
  <p>
    Where a client authorizes us to manage their advertising, we access their
    advertising accounts only with their permission and only to deliver the
    services they have engaged us for. This may include programmatic access to
    advertising platforms through their APIs, including the
    <strong>Google Ads API</strong>, which we use to create, manage, and report
    on campaigns and to build reporting tools for our clients.
  </p>
  <p>
    Any data we access through these platforms is used solely to provide and
    improve the advertising services requested by the client who owns that data.
    We do not sell this data, and we do not use it for any purpose unrelated to
    the services we provide. Our use of information received from Google APIs
    adheres to the applicable Google API Services User Data Policy and Google Ads
    API Terms of Service.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Our website uses cookies and similar technologies to keep the site working,
    understand how it is used, and improve it. You can control cookies through
    your browser settings; disabling some cookies may affect how the site works.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing information</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal information. We share information only with
    service providers who help us operate our business (such as hosting and
    analytics providers), with a client in relation to their own campaigns, or
    where required by law.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention and security</h2>
  <p>
    We keep information only as long as needed for the purposes described here or
    as required by law, and we use reasonable technical and organizational
    measures to protect it against unauthorized access, loss, or misuse.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, or
    delete your personal information, or to object to certain processing. To make
    a request, contact us at
    <a href="mailto:info@cookiesandtokens.com">info@cookiesandtokens.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will
    revise the "Last updated" date above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy or your data? Email
    <a href="mailto:info@cookiesandtokens.com">info@cookiesandtokens.com</a> or
    visit our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
